OHE()¶

For transformation of the categorical features of dataframe into ones for use in ML

In [2]:
def OHE(df):
    
    #Load Label Encoder
    from sklearn.preprocessing import LabelEncoder
    labelEncoder = LabelEncoder()

    #For all Categorical Features, Using OHE, will be transformed for ML to handle.
    for column in list(df.dtypes[(df.dtypes == object)|(df.dtypes == bool)].index):
        df[column] = labelEncoder.fit_transform(df[column].values)
        
    #Return transformed dataframe
    return df

ConfusionMatrix()¶

For visualization of the Confusion Matrix of a model

In [3]:
def ConfusionMatrix(y_test, treePred):
    
    # Create Confusion Matrix via arrays
    from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix
    cf_matrix = confusion_matrix(y_test, treePred)
    
    #Turn those arrays into a single dimension than can then be unpacked into varibles
    tn, fp, fn, tp = cf_matrix.ravel()

    #Graph Confusion Matrix using those 4 varibles which will represent the 4 areas of this graph.
    figure(figsize(10,7))
    
    from matplotlib import colors
    
    #Colors of plot (Red = False, Green = True)
                                        #Red - Green - Green - Red
    cmap = colors.ListedColormap(['#E64905','#0A925B','#0A925B','#E64905'])
    
    #Boundaries of Plot
    bounds=[-0.5, 0.5, 1.5, 2.5, 3.5]
    norm = colors.BoundaryNorm(bounds, cmap.N)
    
    #Use heatmap as template for Confusion Matrix
    heatmap = pcolor(array([[0,1],[2,3]]), cmap=cmap, norm=norm)
    
    #Label the 4 areas of the graph with their respective values and names
    text(x=0.35,y=1.35,s=f"TP\n{tp}",size=30) #True Positive
    text(x=1.35,y=1.35,s=f"FP\n{fp}",size=30) #False Positive
    text(x=0.35,y=0.35,s=f"FN\n{fn}",size=30) #False Negative
    text(x=1.35,y=0.35,s=f"TN\n{tn}",size=30) #True Negative
    
    #Remove the outlines of the plot for each side
    for side in ['bottom','top','right','left']:
        gca().spines[side].set_visible(False)

    #Remove x and y axis ticks
    xticks([])
    yticks([])
    
    #True Class Label usine title
    title("True Class\nPositive                 Negative",size=30)
    
    #Predicted Class Label using ylabel
    ylabel("Predicted Class\nNegative     Positive",size=30)
    
    #Show Plot
    show()

ConfusionStats()¶

Will be used to gather information on the following about a specific model:

for each dataset:

    for each target value:
  • Dataset
  • Features
  • Target
  • AUC
  • Accuracy
  • Precision
  • Recall
  • F1-Score
  • Frequency
  • Deltas of metrics listed for comparision between training and test datasets
In [4]:
def ConfusionStats(model,X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test):
    
    #libraries Used:
    from sklearn.metrics import confusion_matrix
    from sklearn.metrics import roc_auc_score
    
    #Data Container for Final Results
    ConfusionDF = []
    
    #For Each Dataset (Train or Test), metrics will be gathered for comparison
    for dataset, y, X in zip(['Train','Test'],[y_train,y_test],[X_train,X_test]):
        
        #Generate Confusion metric
        cf_matrix = confusion_matrix(y, model.predict(X))
        
        #Unpaxck results into 4 varibles
        tn, fp, fn, tp = cf_matrix.ravel()
        
        #Calculate accuracy and auc which are the same for both 0 and 1 target varible: 
        accuracy = (tp+tn)/(tp+tn+fp+fn)
        auc = roc_auc_score(y, model.decision_function(X))
        
        #Recird features used:
        features = list(X.columns)
        
        #For each target varible (0 or 1), metrics will be gathered for comparison
        for target, trueTarget, falseTarget, flaseOtherTarget in zip([0,1],[tn,tp],[fn,fp],[fp,fn]):
            
            #Calculate precision or positive predictive value
            precision = trueTarget/(trueTarget+falseTarget)
            
            #Calculate recal or Sensitivity or True Positive rate
            recall = trueTarget/(trueTarget+flaseOtherTarget)
            
            #Harmonic mean of recal and precision
            f1 = 2*((precision*recall)/(precision+recall))
            
            #Append all results gathered so far into the final data container
            ConfusionDF.append([dataset,features,target,auc,accuracy,precision,recall,f1,y.value_counts()[target]])
    
    #Once the loop is finished, convert final data container into a dataframe
    ConfusionDF = pd.DataFrame(ConfusionDF,columns=['Dataset',
                                                    'Features',
                                                    'Target',
                                                    'AUC',
                                                    'Accuracy',
                                                    'Precision',
                                                    'Recall',
                                                    'F1-Score',
                                                    'Frequency']).round(4)
    
    #Focus data analysis on specific metrics of 'AUC','Accuracy','Precision','Recall','F1-Score' based on dataset
    #and specific target value
    metrics = ConfusionDF.drop(['Features','Frequency'],axis=1).set_index(['Dataset','Target'])

    #Final Data contianer for Metric Deltas (Difference between training and test datasets)
    df = []
    df.append([nan,nan,nan,nan]) #Training Dataset Delta - Not a priority
    df.append([nan,nan,nan,nan]) #Training Dataset Delta - Not a priority
    
    #For specific target (0 - 1), Difference between training and test datasets 
    for target in [0,1]:
        df.append((metrics.loc[('Train',target)]-metrics.loc[('Test',target)]).values.tolist())
    
    #Add new metric deltas to the final dataframe
    ConfusionDF = pd.concat([ConfusionDF,pd.DataFrame(df,columns=[f'{col}_Delta' 
                                                                  for col in metrics.columns])],axis=1)
    #return final dataframe for use in evalulation of model
    return ConfusionDF

GBT()¶

In [5]:
def GBT(data,min_samples_split,min_samples_leaf,n_estimators,learning_rate,max_depth):
    from sklearn.ensemble import GradientBoostingClassifier
    start = time.time()
    
    X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = data
    
    model = GradientBoostingClassifier(min_samples_split = min_samples_split,
                                       min_samples_leaf = min_samples_leaf,
                                       n_estimators=n_estimators,
                                       learning_rate=learning_rate,
                                       max_depth=max_depth,
                                       max_features = 'sqrt',
                                       random_state=0).fit(X_train, y_train)
    
    print(f"{time.time() - start} seconds")
    
    columns = ['Model','Features','Dataset', 'Target', 'AUC', 'Accuracy', 'Precision', 'Recall', 'F1-Score', 
               'Frequency', 'AUC_Delta','Accuracy_Delta', 'Precision_Delta', 'Recall_Delta','F1-Score_Delta']
    
    return [model] + ConfusionStats(model,X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test).loc[3].tolist(),columns

calcuate_roc_curve()¶

In [6]:
def calcuate_roc_curve(model,X_test):
    from sklearn.metrics import roc_curve
    fpr, tpr, thresholds = roc_curve(y_test, model.decision_function(X_test))
    return (model,fpr, tpr, thresholds)

def Graph_AUC(models_list,X_test):
    from sklearn.metrics import roc_auc_score

    figure(figsize(10,6))

    #For every model for comparison
    for model,fpr, tpr, thresholds in models_list:
        
        #Plot Model Curve
        plot(fpr, tpr, label=f"{str(model).split('(')[0]} - AUC: {round(roc_auc_score(y_test, model.decision_function(X_test)),2)}")
        fill_between(fpr,tpr,alpha=0.2)
        
        #Find threshold closest to zero
        close_zero = np.argmin(np.abs(thresholds))
        plot(fpr[close_zero], tpr[close_zero], 'o', markersize=10, fillstyle="full", c='black', mew=2)

        #Threshold Value
        text(fpr[close_zero]+0.020, tpr[close_zero]-0.030,f'{round(tpr[close_zero],2)}\n{round(fpr[close_zero],2)}')
    
    #Used only for legend()
    plot(0, 0, 'o', markersize=1,label="threshold zeros", fillstyle="full", c='black', mew=2)
    
    #Labels
    xlabel("False Positive Rate",size=15)
    ylabel("True Positive Rate (recall)",size=15)
    title('ROC Curve',size=20)

    #Baseline
    plot([0, 1], [0, 1], color='red', linestyle='--',label='Baseline - AUC: 0.50')

    #Remove plot boundaries
    for side in ["right","top","bottom","left"]:
            gca().spines[side].set_visible(False)

    #Remove ticks
    xticks([])
    yticks([])

    #New Boundaries
    plot([0, 1], [0, 0],'-',color='red')   #Good Corner
    plot([1, 1], [0, 1],'-',color='red')   #Good Corner
    plot([0, 1], [1, 1],'-',color='green') #Bad Corner
    plot([0, 0], [0, 1],'-',color='green') #Bad Corner

    #New Range Labels
    text(-0.025,-0.05,'0',size=20)
    text(1.025,-0.05,'1',size=20)
    text(-0.025,1.05,'1',size=20)

    #Legend
    legend(bbox_to_anchor=(1, 0.35),fontsize=20)

    show()

Graph_Model_Metrics()¶

In [8]:
def Graph_Model_Metrics(results):
    figure(figsize(11,7))

    #Columns for results
    metrics = results.columns[4:-6] #Metrics Columns
    deltas = results.columns[-5:]   #Delta Columns

    #Calculate Training Results
    results_train = pd.DataFrame(results[metrics].values + results[deltas].values,columns = metrics)

    # Graph Training and Testing results for each Metric
    for metric in metrics:

        #Change Opacity based on condition to allow visiblility of both train and test
        if results_train[metric].values[0] > results[metric].values[0]:
            alpha = 1
        else:
            alpha = 0.8

        bar(metric,1,color='black')                           #Maximum Value
        bar(metric,results_train[metric],color='red')         #Training Metric
        bar(metric,results[metric],color='green',alpha=alpha) #Testing Metric

    #Remove plot boundaries
    for side in ["right","top","bottom","left"]:
        gca().spines[side].set_visible(False)

    #Labels & Ticks
    yticks([])
    xticks(size=18)
    title("Key Model Metrics",size=25)

    #Testing Data Labels
    for i, v in enumerate(results[metrics].values[0]):
        text(i, v-0.05, f'{round(v,4)}', color='black', fontsize=15, ha='center', va='center')  

    #Training Data Labels
    for i, v in enumerate(results_train[metrics].values[0]):
        text(i, v+0.05, f'{round(v,4)}', color='red', fontsize=15, ha='center', va='center')  

    text(-0.8,1,'1.0',size=15)

    #Legend
    legend(['Maximum','Train','Test'],fontsize=20,loc=(1,0))

    #Plot Results
    show()

importanceDf()¶

In [27]:
def importanceDf(features,model):
    return pd.DataFrame([[C,I] for C,I in zip(features.columns,model.feature_importances_)],columns = ['Feature','Importance']).sort_values('Importance',ascending=False)

def importanceDf(features,model):
    return pd.DataFrame([[C,I] for C,I in zip(features.columns,model.coef_)],columns = ['Feature','Importance']).sort_values('Importance',ascending=False)

classification_df()¶

In [47]:
def classification_df(y_test, y_pred):
    # classification Report
    from sklearn.metrics import classification_report
    cols = ['Target'] + [col for col in [row for row in classification_report(y_test, y_pred).split("\n")][0].strip().split("  ") if col != '']
    classification_df = pd.DataFrame([row.strip().split('     ') for row in classification_report(y_test, y_pred).split("\n")[2:4]],columns=cols)
    return classification_df

Logistic Regression Loop¶

In this section, a loop will be utilized to find the optimal logistic regression. The data was split 70-30. The parameters are a list of features and desired number of features out of that list. The loop then returns both the highest test set accuracy and the features needed to achieve that.¶

In [53]:
import itertools
from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression
from sklearn import metrics
import time
def create_lists(complete_list_of_elements,desired_elements):
    if desired_elements > len(complete_list_of_elements):
        print ("ERROR ==> desired elements is longer that the lenght of the list")
        return None

    all_lists = itertools.combinations(complete_list_of_elements,desired_elements)
    temp_list = [",".join(index) for index in all_lists]

    list_to_be_returned = []

    for current_list in temp_list:
        split_list = current_list.split(",")
        list_to_be_returned.append(split_list)

    print ("Total models: {}".format(len(list_to_be_returned)))
    return list_to_be_returned


model_features = create_lists(['Coverage_Level_Code', 'Coverage_Level_Parent',
'Member_Status', 'Renew_Method','Count_Clicks_or_Opens', 'Children',
'Credit_RangesDecode', 'Dwelling_Type',
'Email_Prefrence_For_At_least_One_Product',
'Email_Pref_Your_AAA_Digital', 'Est_Household_IncomeDecode',
'FSV_CMSI_Flag', 'FSV_Credit_Card_Flag', 'FSV_ID_Theft_Flag',
'FSV_TCI_Flag', 'Occupation_Group', 'Net_Worth', 'Race', 'Member_Dues_Three_Years', 'ERS_Member_Cost_Three_Years',
       'ERS_ENT_Count_Three_Years'],20)

accuracy_to_featues = {}

counter = 0
for current_model in model_features:
    X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(filtered_df[current_model], AAA_Combined['Auto'], train_size=0.7, random_state=0)
    start = time.time()
    LogReg = LogisticRegression(max_iter=10000)
    LogReg.fit(X_train, y_train)
    y_pred = LogReg.predict(X_test)
    print(f"{time.time() - start} seconds")
    acc_logreg = metrics.accuracy_score(y_test,y_pred) * 100
    acc_logreg
    accuracy_to_featues[acc_logreg] = current_model
    counter+=1
    print("[{}/{}] models trained, accuracy: {}".format(counter,len(model_features),acc_logreg))
 

highest_scores = max(list(accuracy_to_featues.keys()))

print('')

highest_score_features = accuracy_to_featues[highest_scores]
print(highest_scores,highest_score_features)

def classification_df(y_test, treePred):
    # classification Report
    from sklearn.metrics import classification_report
    cols = ['Target'] + [col for col in [row for row in classification_report(y_test, treePred).split("\n")][0].strip().split("  ") if col != '']
    classification_df = pd.DataFrame([row.strip().split('     ') for row in classification_report(y_test, treePred).split("\n")[2:4]],columns=cols)
    return classification_df
def importanceDf(features,model):
    return pd.DataFrame([[C,I] for C,I in zip(features.columns,model.feature_importances_)],columns = ['Feature','Importance']).sort_values('Importance',ascending=False)

import time
def create_lists(complete_list_of_elements,desired_elements):
    if desired_elements > len(complete_list_of_elements):
        print ("ERROR ==> desired elements is longer that the lenght of the list")
        return None

    all_lists = itertools.combinations(complete_list_of_elements,desired_elements)
    temp_list = [",".join(index) for index in all_lists]

    list_to_be_returned = []

    for current_list in temp_list:
        split_list = current_list.split(",")
        list_to_be_returned.append(split_list)

    print ("Total models: {}".format(len(list_to_be_returned)))
    return list_to_be_returned


model_features = create_lists(['Coverage_Level_Code', 'Coverage_Level_Parent', 'Member_Status',
       'Member_Tenure_Years', 'Renew_Method', 'Count_Clicks_or_Opens', 'Children',
        'Credit_RangesDecode','Dwelling_Type', 'Email_Pref_Your_AAA_Digital','FSV_CMSI_Flag', 'FSV_Credit_Card_Flag', 
        'FSV_ID_Theft_Flag', 'Occupation_Group','Marital_Status', 'Net_Worth', 'Race', 'Total_Travel_Records', 'year',
        'Member_Dues_Three_Years'],19)

accuracy_to_featues = {}

counter = 0
for current_model in model_features:
    X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(filtered_df[current_model], AAA_Combined['Home'], train_size=0.7, random_state=0)
    start = time.time()
    LogReg = LogisticRegression(max_iter=10000)
    LogReg.fit(X_train, y_train)
    y_pred = LogReg.predict(X_test)
    print(f"{time.time() - start} seconds")
    acc_logreg = metrics.accuracy_score(y_test,y_pred) * 100
    acc_logreg
    accuracy_to_featues[acc_logreg] = current_model
    counter+=1
    print("[{}/{}] models trained, accuracy: {}".format(counter,len(model_features),acc_logreg))
 

highest_scores = max(list(accuracy_to_featues.keys()))

print('')

highest_score_features = accuracy_to_featues[highest_scores]
print(highest_scores,highest_score_features)
